##Editing Audio
details of editing audio

Each of the following options can be achieved by clicking 'esc' and selecting the appropriate option.

NOTE: After finishing, don't forget to click 'esc' again and press '1' to come back to the regular cursor.

*Trimming
*Cutting - Esc + 5 brings you to the cutting tool.(only for versions prior to Logic Pro X)
*Grid (ctrl + G)
*Change grid resolution
*modifier key to toggle grid
*add fades
*modify fades
*efficient compiling of multiple takes

##Efficient Editing
details of efficient editing
*Zoom - You can zoom in and out by pressing ctl+option+ up/down to zoom in and out (default). Also, pinch zoom works. At least in LP9.
*(Command + left arrow = zooms horizontally in , Command + right arrow (keyboard) = zoom horizontally out, vertical zoom in and out is command + up and down arrows in Logic Pro X)
*Nudge
*Cycle
*Merge
*Name
*Color
*Markers
*Change tempo
*Other efficient editing tips

##Editing MIDI
details of editing midi
*Velocity: In piano roll view, select Velocity tool (V) and move up/down to increase velocity. To change all velocities at once, enter in Hypereditor mode (option+5) and select all velocities and move it. 
*Quantization: In piano roll view,select grid notes (1/8, 1/16, swing, ...), select notes and press Q button.
*Control Change data
*MIDI monitor(through)
*Other MIDI editing tips
*Adding software instruments
*Other MIDI tips

